## CK-X Compose configuration (example)

# Docker Hub namespace for prebuilt images
# e.g., je01, myorg, or your Docker Hub user
CKX_IMAGE_NS=je01

# Version tag for the image set that contains the most detailed exam3 assets
# Coordinate all services on the same version to avoid drift
CKX_VERSION=exam3-v2

# Optional: force a specific platform for all services
# Examples:
CKX_PLATFORM=linux/arm64   # Apple Silicon hosts
#   CKX_PLATFORM=linux/amd64   # x86_64 hosts
# Leave blank to let Docker auto-select
# CKX_PLATFORM=

# Optional per-service image overrides (full image:tag strings)
# If set, these take precedence over CKX_IMAGE_NS/CKX_VERSION
# REMOTE_DESKTOP_IMAGE=je01/ckx-remote-desktop:exam3-v2
# WEBAPP_IMAGE=je01/ckx-webapp:exam3-v2
# NGINX_IMAGE=je01/ckx-nginx:exam3-v2
# JUMPHOST_IMAGE=je01/ckx-jumphost:exam3-v2
# REMOTE_TERMINAL_IMAGE=je01/ckx-remote-terminal:exam3-v2
# CLUSTER_IMAGE=je01/ckx-cluster:exam3-v2
# FACILITATOR_IMAGE=je01/ckx-facilitator:exam3-v2

# Optional: pin volume names to avoid project-prefixed variants
# CKX_COURSE_VOLUME=ckx-course-data
# CKX_KUBECONFIG_VOLUME=ckx-kube-config
